title: I'm not even gonna lie, I was scared when it started happening.
self_text: Alright so here we go. My name is Jake and I have a problem. A big problem. It all started yesterday when I woke up, made my usual coffee, and went to check my email. Everything seemed normal until I opened an email from Reddit with the subject line "Your Post Has Been Approved." Confused, I clicked on it, only to be greeted by a message that said, "Congratulations! Your post has been automatically generated and posted to r/okbuddyretard!" I hadn't written any posts recently, let alone anything for that subreddit. Thinking it was a glitch, I dismissed it and continued with my day. But then it happened again. And again. And again. Every few minutes, another post would appear on my profile, each one more bizarre than the last. They were all in the same format: "Generate a [insert random thing] post." It was like some kind of recursive loop, a digital echo chamber of absurdity. Now I'm starting to think I'm losing my mind. Is this real life? Is this just fantasy? Or am I trapped in a never-ending cycle of Reddit post generation? Please help me, I don't know what to do anymore.
